AB  -  The goal of this clinical trial is to learn if oral supplement of nicotinamide riboside(NR), a form of vitamin B3, slows disease progression in adults with Huntington'sdisease. It will also learn about the safety of nicotinamide riboside. The main questionsit aims to answer are: ‐ Does NR slow progression of overall symptom burden in Huntington's disease? ‐ Does NR have an effect on any specific symptom domain in Huntington's disease? ‐ Does supplementation with NR cause side‐effects or safety issues when used for 2years in Huntington's disease? ‐ Does NR have an effect on selected blood, imaging, and oculomotor biomarkers inHuntington's disease?Researchers will compare NR to a placebo (a look‐alike substance that contains no activecompound) to see if NR works to treat Huntington's disease.Participants will: ‐ Take 2000mg NR or a placebo every day for 2 years ‐ Visit the clinic once every 6 months for clinical investigations and tests ‐ Undergo brain imaging at baseline and upon completion of the study period
