AB  -  INTERVENTION: Product Name: , Product Code:PRD9949387, Pharmaceutical Form: DISPERSION FOR INFUSION, Other descriptive name: , Strength: , Product Name: , Product Code:SCP16294414, Pharmaceutical Form: , Other descriptive name: , Strength: , Product Name: , Product Code:SCP5487322, Pharmaceutical Form: , Other descriptive name: , Strength: , Product Name: METHOXSALEN, Product Code:SUB14541MIG, Pharmaceutical Form: SOLUTION FOR BLOOD FRACTION MODIFICATION, Other descriptive name: , Strength: , Product Name: , Product Code:SCP149129, Pharmaceutical Form: , Other descriptive name: , Strength: , Product Name: , Product Code:SCP8222764, Pharmaceutical Form: , Other descriptive name: , Strength: CONDITION: MedDRA version: 20.1Level: PTClassification code: 10066260Term: Acute graft versus host disease Class: 100000004870 Steroid refractory Acute Graft versus host Disease ; MedDRA version: 20.1Level: PTClassification code: 10066260Term: Acute graft versus host disease Class: 100000004870 Therapeutic area: Diseases [C] ‐ Immune System Diseases [C20] PRIMARY OUTCOME: Main Objective: Comparative evaluation of the overall response rate in paediatric participants with steroid‐refractory acute graft‐versus‐host disease (SR aGvHD) at Visit Day 28 after treatment with MC0518 or first used best available therapy (BAT) Primary end point(s): Overall response (OR), defined as complete response (CR) or partial response (PR) at Visit Day 28 relative to the aGvHD status at baseline (Visit Day 1 prior to the first treatment)., CR is defined as resolution of aGvHD in all involved organs. PR is defined as improvement in at least 1 stage in 1 or more organs involved with aGvHD symptoms without progression in others., No response (NR) is defined as the absence of CR or PR. Death before Visit Day 28 will be considered NR. The addition of or change to any further systemic therapy (except changes in steroid treatment) after first administration of MC0518 / first used BAT before Visit Day 28 will be considered NR. Secondary Objective: Comparative evaluation of freedom from treatment failure defined by the absence of death, malignancy relapse or progression, or addition of or change to any further systemic acute graft‐versus‐host disease (aGvHD) therapy within 6 months after randomisation and prior to diagnosis of chronic graft versus‐host disease (cGvHD), Comparative evaluation of further secondary efficacy endpoints with respect to overall survival (OS) and response to treatment, Comparative evaluation of the safety, Comparative evaluation of health‐related quality of life (HRQoL) SECONDARY OUTCOME: Secondary end point(s):aGvHD response at Visit Day 28 assessed by CR, PR, and NR and at Visit Day 60, Visit Day 100, and Visit Day 180 assessed by OR, CR, PR, and NR relative to baseline Secondary end point(s):Best OR until Visit Day 28, defined as the achievement of an OR at any time point up to and including Visit Day 28 Secondary end point(s):Change of aGvHD grade at Visit Day 8, Visit Day 15, Visit Day 22, Visit Day 28, Visit Day 60, Visit Day 100, and Visit Day 180 relative to baseline Secondary end point(s):Cumulative dose of steroids given for SR‐aGvHD per kg body weight (BW) from the date of the first treatment administration until Visit Day 28, Visit Day 60, and until Visit Month 24 Secondary end point(s):Duration of response until Visit Month 24, defined as the time from the date of the first OR (CR or PR) to the date of aGvHD assessed as NR compared to the baseline assessment, or the date of addition of or change to any further systemic aGvHD therapy (except changes in steroid treatment), in responders Secondary end point(s):Event free survival until Visit Month 24, defined as the time from the date of randomisation to the date of the event. An event is defined as GF, relapse or progression of the underlying disease, or death due to any cause Secondary end point(s):Freedom from treatment failure until 6 months (Visit Day 180), defined as the time from the date of randomisation to the date of the event. An event is defined as death, relapse or progression of the underlying disease, or addition of or change to any further systemic aGvHD therapy (except changes in steroid treatment). The diagnosis of cGvHD is a competing event Secondary end point(s):HRQoL measures: Paediatric Quality of Life InventoryTM (PedsQL™) 4.0 Generic Core Scales with the PedsQL™ Stem Cell Transplant Module at Visit Day 28, Visit Day 60, Visit Day 100, and Visit Day 180 compared to baseline Secondary end point(s):Incidence of and time to cGvHD from Visit Day 60 until Visit Month 24 Secondary end point(s):Incidence of and time to relapse or progression of the underlying disease in participants with underlying malignant disease from randomisation until Visit Month 24 Secondary end point(s):Incidence of graft failure (GF) from baseline until Visit Month 24 Secondary end point(s):Non‐relapse mortality until Visit Month 24, defined as the time from the date of randomisation to the date of the event. An event is defined as death without previous relapse or progression of the underlying disease. Relapse or progression are competing events Secondary end point(s):OS until Visit Month 24, defined as the time from the date of randomisation to the date of death due to any cause Secondary end point(s):Performance score (Karnofsky / Lansky scale) at Visit Day 8, Visit Day 15, Visit Day 22, Visit Day 28, Visit Day 60, and Visit Day 100 compared to baseline Secondary end point(s):The incidence and severity of all adverse events (AEs), including viral, bacterial, and fungal infections until Visit Day 60, and of adverse reactions (ARs) until Visit Month 24 Secondary end point(s):Time to response, defined as the time from the date of the first treatment administration to the date of the first response (CR or PR) INCLUSION CRITERIA: Participant had a previous allogeneic HSCT as indicated for non‐malignant (including inborn errors of metabolism, primary immunodeficiencies, haemoglobinopathies, and bone marrow failure syndromes) or haematological malignant disease or neuroblastoma., Participant has been clinically diagnosed with Grade II to IV aGvHD according to Harris et al. A biopsy of the involved organs with aGvHD is encouraged but not required., Participant has experienced failure of previous first line aGvHD treatment (ie, SR aGvHD), defined as: ‐ aGvHD progression within 3 to 5 days of therapy onset with = 2 mg/kg/day of prednisone equivalent or ‐ failure to improve within 5 to 7 days of treatment initiation with = 2 mg/kg/day of prednisone equivalent or ‐ incomplete response after > 28 days of immunosuppressive treatment including at least 5 days with = 2 mg/kg/day of prednisone equivalent., Male or female participant who is = 28 days and < 18 years of age and has a minimum BW of 3.2 kg a
