AB  -  INTERVENTION: Biological/Vaccine, Non‐Stem Cell : Subjects who met the final selection/exclusion criteria from the Baseline were randomly assigned to the test group (Eucept‐administered group) or the control group (standard anti‐inflammatory analgesic group). During the 12‐week trial period, the randomized subjects visited the trial site at baseline (week 0), 4 weeks, 8 weeks, and 12 weeks, and evaluated efficacy and adverse events. The standard treatment for the control group is treatment including existing NSAIDs and DMARDs (sulfasalazine), and the patients assigned to the test group will receive Eucept 50mg subcutaneously once a week. CONDITION: Diseases of the musculoskeletal system and connective tissue PRIMARY OUTCOME: Assessment of spondyloarthritis international society 20 response(ASAS 20) SECONDARY OUTCOME: 44‐swelling and tender joints Ankylosing Spondylitis Disease Activity Score‐ C reactive protein(ASDASCRP) Assessment of spondyloarthritis international society Health Index Bath Ankylosing Spondylitis Disease Activity Index Bath ankylosing spondylitis functional index(BASFI) Bath Ankylosing Spondylitis Metrology Inde X(BASMI) Maastricht Ankylosing Spondylitis Enthesitis Score (MASES) MRI SIJ Spondyloarthritis Research Consortium Canada (SPARCC) score Number of adverse events INCLUSION CRITERIA: 1. Subjects greater than 18 years of age 2. Patients fulfilling the ASAS classification criteria for axial SpA including both non radiographic axial spondyloarthritis (nr‐A XSpA) and ankylosing spondylitis(AS) 3. Evidence of bone marrow edema on SI joint MRI or elevation of hsCRP 4. BASDAI =4 5. Total back pain VAS = 40 mm (0‐100 mm) 6. Patients with axSpA underwent a trial of at least 2 course of NSAIDs with optimum doses for at least 1 month without response or with partial response
