e. At progression 8/19 pts crossed over from abiraterone to olaparib and 8/21 pts vice versa. Median (95% CI) PFS from crossover to: olaparib 8.3 m (5.5, 15), abiraterone 7.2 m (2.8, NR). Median (95% CI) PFS from randomization: olaparib 16 m (7.8‐25) and abiraterone 16 m (11‐28). RR to crossover treatment: olaparib 38% and abiraterone 25%. PSA RR to crossover treatment: olaparib 50% and abiraterone 63%. Conclusions: In mCRPC pts with BRCA1/2 or ATM alterations, abiraterone/prednisone + olaparib was well tolerated and resulted in a longer PFS vs either agent alone or sequentially.
