AB  -  INTERVENTION: Anatomic resection group(AR):Anatomic resection;Nonanatomic resection group(NR):Nonanatomic resection; CONDITION: HBV‐associated hepatocellular carcinoma PRIMARY OUTCOME: Blood test indicators: 1. alpha‐fetoprotein variant L3; 2. Interleukin 10; 3. Interleukin 12; 4. transforming growth factor ß.;Pathological examination indicators: 1. microvascular invasion; 2. carcinoma cell differentiation; 3. M1 macrophage; 4. M2 macrophage; 5. tumor size; 6. the number of tumor;Data related to the operation: 1. operation time; 2. time of vascular clamping; 3. intraoperative bleeding; 4. time of hepatectomy; 5. Intraoperative ultrasound results.;Postoperative complications: (1) wound infection; (2) hepatic cross section infection; (3) abdominal cavity hemorrhage; (4) liver failure; (5)bile leakage.;Postoperative recovery related data: 1. exhaust time; 2. feeding time; 3. Abdominal drainage time; 4. off‐bed activity time; 5. postoperative hospital stay; 6. The total cost.;Postoperative follow‐up: 1. Color Doppler ultrasound, Enhanced CT; 2. alpha‐fetoprotein variant L3; 3. recurrence rate operation.; INCLUSION CRITERIA: 1. The patients age between 18 and 75 years,including male and female.Diagnosis of hepatocellular carcinoma for the first time; 2. HBsAg is positive; 3. Not beyond hemihepatic metastasis, In order to radical resection; 4. Liver function being Child‐Pugh A.
