AB  -  INTERVENTION: Group 1: Group Nr.1 receives a detailed video‐assisted consent including a detailed video, written and verbal consent. They undergo a questionnaire‐based testing of anxiety and satisfaction. In addition, artefacts of the radiological images will be evaluated. Group 2: Group Nr.2 receives a basic video‐assisted consent including a simple video, written and verbal consent. They undergo a questionnaire‐based testing of anxiety and satisfaction. In addition, artefacts of the radiological images will be evaluated. Group 3: Group Nr.3 receives only written and verbal consent. They undergo a questionnaire‐based testing of anxiety and satisfaction. In addition, artefacts of the radiological images will be evaluated. CONDITION: Acute myocardial infarction Aortic (valve) stenosis Atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease, so described Heart failure I25.0 I35.0 I40.0 Infective myocarditis prothesis‐thrombosis of cardiac valvular implants ; I25.0 ; I40.0 ; I50 ; I35.0 ; I21 PRIMARY OUTCOME: Patient’s anxiety quantified with the STAI (State‐trait‐Anxiety‐Inventory) and self‐made scales SECONDARY OUTCOME: Patient’s satisfaction ; Physiological parameters during the examination (Heartrate and blood pressure) ; Quality and artefacts of images INCLUSION CRITERIA: ‐ Patients undergoing cardiac CT before transcatheter aortic valve implantation (TAVI), cardiac CT to exclude coronary heart disease (CHC), cardiac MRI to exclude myocarditis or ischemic cardiomyopathy or other cardiac MRI ‐ all participants have to be capable of giving consent and have to voluntarily agree to participate in the trial ‐ speak German fluently
