AB  -  INTERVENTION: Experimental Group A total of 46 patients received antimicrobial photodynamic therapy (aPDT) using a red laser (660 nm). Immediately after tooth extraction, the allocated socket for the aPDT group was irrigated with saline solution (0.9%). After aspiration, the socket was filled with the photosensitizer agent (methylene blue 0.01%). Following a 5‐minute waiting period, the excess dye was removed, and the region was irradiated using a Gallium‐Aluminum‐Arsenide diode laser (Photon‐lase III ‐ DMC Importation and Exportation of Equipment LTDA, São Carlos, São Paulo, Brazil). The laser was applied continuously in contact and spot mode with the following parameters: red wavelength (660 nm), power output of 100 mW, spot size of 0.028 cm², and an energy density of 107 J/cm². The laser tip was positioned directly in contact with three specific points in the socket area. During irradiation, the equipment emitted audible signals. Each point received 9 J of energy (total energy: 27 J) for 30 seconds per point. The three irradiation points were:Middle third of the lingual surface , Middle third of the buccal surface ,Central region of the alveolus when aPDT Combined with Photobiomodulation (PBM) by Infrared Laser (808 nm) Following the application of aPDT as described above, the socket was irrigated with saline solution (0.9%) and sutured. Subsequently, photobiomodulation (PBM) with an infrared laser was applied using the following parameters: wavelength of 808 nm, spot size of 0.028 cm², power output of 0.1 W, energy density of 3.6 W/cm², 89 J/cm², and 2.5 J per point in contact with the same three irradiation points. however, For the Sham group, the laser tip was positioned at the same three points as described for the aPDT group, simulating PBM treatment. CONDITION: Diabetic Patient PRIMARY OUTCOME: Evaluate Socket repair by digital periapical x‐ray images computed analysis cusing the &amp;quot;freehand drawing&amp;quot; tool in Image J software (NIH ‐ USA) to assess the radiolucent area of the socket and the bone neoformation density between 7 , 30,60 days postoperative periods; INCLUSION CRITERIA: Type 2 diabetic patients of both genders; age between 35 and 60 years; requiring extraction of erupted permanent teeth, either by simple alveolar techniques or comple Xopen flap extractions; clinical and laboratory examinations performed to standardize the sample; fasting blood glucose levels between 110 and 250 mg/dl; glycated hemoglobin (HbA1c) values up to 7.5%; controlled hypertension with an average blood pressure up to 150/100 mmHg SECONDARY OUTCOME: Evaluate the mucosal socket repair after 7 days postoperatively by a digital image scale, pain levels through a visual analog scale applied in a diary in different timepoints at 4, 6, 8, 12, 24, and 48 hours of the postoperative period, ; edema measurements of anatomic face in Five linear measurements (mm) were taken: gonial angle to the tragus (Ag‐Tr), gonial angle to the corner of the eye (Ag‐Co), gonial angle to the edge of the nose (Ag‐Nr), gonial angle to the labial commissure (Ag‐Cl), and from the gonial angle to the tissue edge of the pogonion (Ag‐Pg). ; before extraction and 7 days after extraction and mouth ; opening limitation through the differences between intermaxillary distance ; before extraction and before extraction and 7 days after extraction that will be provided with ; by digital caliper
